ivardefs.name: contact_
ivardefs.desc: Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher.

ivardefs.name: copyright
ivardefs.desc: A copyright statement relating to the test script and/or its contents. Copyright statements are generally legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the test script.

ivardefs.name: date
ivardefs.desc: The date  (and optionally time) when the test script was published. The date must change if and when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the test script

ivardefs.name: description
ivardefs.desc: A free text natural language description of the test script from a consumer's perspective.

ivardefs.name: destination_
ivardefs.desc: An abstract server used in operations within this test script in the destination element.

ivardefs.name: experimental
ivardefs.desc: A boolean value to indicate that this test script is authored for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing), and is not intended to be used for genuine usage.

ivardefs.name: fixture_
ivardefs.desc: Fixture in the test script - by reference (uri). All fixtures are required for the test script to execute.

ivardefs.name: identifier
ivardefs.desc: A formal identifier that is used to identify this test script when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance.

ivardefs.name: jurisdiction_
ivardefs.desc: A legal or geographic region in which the test script is intended to be used.

ivardefs.name: metadata
ivardefs.desc: The required capability must exist and are assumed to function correctly on the FHIR server being tested.

ivardefs.name: name
ivardefs.desc: A natural language name identifying the test script. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation.

ivardefs.name: origin_
ivardefs.desc: An abstract server used in operations within this test script in the origin element.

ivardefs.name: profile_
ivardefs.desc: Reference to the profile to be used for validation.

ivardefs.name: publisher
ivardefs.desc: The name of the individual or organization that published the test script.

ivardefs.name: purpose
ivardefs.desc: Explaination of why this test script is needed and why it has been designed as it has.

ivardefs.name: ruleset_
ivardefs.desc: Contains one or more rules.  Offers a way to group rules so assertions could reference the group of rules and have them all applied.

ivardefs.name: rule_
ivardefs.desc: Assert rule to be used in one or more asserts within the test script.

ivardefs.name: setup
ivardefs.desc: A series of required setup operations before tests are executed.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The status of this test script. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content.

ivardefs.name: teardown
ivardefs.desc: A series of operations required to clean up after the all the tests are executed (successfully or otherwise).

ivardefs.name: test_
ivardefs.desc: A test in this script.

ivardefs.name: title
ivardefs.desc: A short, descriptive, user-friendly title for the test script.

ivardefs.name: url
ivardefs.desc: An absolute URI that is used to identify this test script when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This SHALL be a URL, SHOULD be globally unique, and SHOULD be an address at which this test script is (or will be) published.

ivardefs.name: useContext_
ivardefs.desc: The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These terms may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate test script instances.

ivardefs.name: variable_
ivardefs.desc: Variable is set based either on element value in response body or on header field value in the response headers.

ivardefs.name: version
